Popular actress Uche Jombo Rodriguez has argued that talent is never enough for anyone in life.  The Nollywood star made this known while weighing in on the rape and assault allegations levelled against Manchester United player, Mason Greenwood. “Talent is never enough, character matters. Being an actual human matter,” she tweeted. Jombo-Rodriguez also gave successful tips on being successful as a producer.  She said; “A logline is about selling your story not telling it. Yes, you can write a brilliant script and not be able to write a good logline for it. It’s ok to ask for help.” The mother of one also revealed one of her favourite films. “Holding Hope, one of my favourite films of mine.” Jombo-Rodriguez co-produced the film, ‘Holding Hope,’ alongside Emem Isong in 2010. The film was written by Uduak Isong Oguamanam and directed by Desmond Elliot. It featured Desmond Elliot, Uche Jombo, Nadia Buari, and Abiola Segun Williams. Veteran Nigerian movie star, Uche Jombo has marked 20 years in the Nigerian movie industry.  Uche Jombo 39 year old Nigerian script write, movie producer and actress Uche Jombo has reached a milestone of 20 solid years in the film industry. UJ as as her friends will like to call her… In "Entertainment" Abuja  -  Omoni Oboli, rising Nollywood producer and actress, will be taking her third movie “Wives on Strike “ to the cinemas on April 8. According to a statement made available to the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on Thursday, “Wives on Strike” is a hilarious comedy about a group… In "Entertainment" President Muhammadu Buhari yesterday addressed the Nation on the outbreak of Coronavirus in Nigeria, and actress, Uche Jombo has reacted to his speech. According to her, President Buhari’s social media team who watched the video and shared it need to be replaced for not “correcting him” She also lamented that… In "Entertainment"